<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-582-516  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 582 516.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  June 18 1990 n373 p143(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Municipal automation: geographic-system project proves successful.andO;(Edmonton, Alberta's Geographic Base Information System)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Doyle, T.C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>City officials in Edmonton, Alberta, have established an automatedinformation storage and retrieval system that improves utilitiesmanagement and performs other vital functions.andP;  The GeographicBase Information System uses replicated maps of streets, utilitiesand properties to retrieve and display information on a network ofcomputer workstations.andP;  Edmonton's system uses graphicsworkstations running MS-DOS, Apple Macintoshes, UNIX workstationsand VAX systems.andP;  Each utility department compiles and transfersdata to a central site.andP;  City officials characterize the GBIS as adecentralized but integrated network system used for mapping,design, graphics, network management and planning.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     CanadaMunicipal GovernmentNetwork ManagementGeographic Information SystemsUtilitiesInformation Storage and Retrieval.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>